  "local_port": 42994,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best coding bootcamps?",
  "response": "The best coding bootcamps can vary depending on your individual needs, such as your learning style, budget, location, and career aspirations. However, here\u2019s a list of some of the most highly regarded coding bootcamps as of late 2023, based on factors like reputation, outcomes, curriculum, and student reviews:\n\n---\n\n1. **General Assembly**  \n   - **Focus**: Full-stack development, data science, UX design, and more.  \n   - **Format**: In-person and online.  \n   - **Known For**: Strong career support and extensive alumni network.  \n\n2. **Flatiron School**  \n   - **Focus**: Software engineering, data science, cybersecurity, and UX/UI design.  \n   - **Format**: Online and in-person (New York City).  \n   - **Known For**: Job placement guarantees (with conditions) and comprehensive curriculum.  \n\n3. **App Academy**  \n   - **Focus**: Full-stack web development.  \n   - **Format**: Online and in-person (New York City, San Francisco).  \n   - **Known For**: Deploy first, pay later (income share agreement) model.  \n\n4. **Hack Reactor (Galvanize)**  \n   - **Focus**: Software engineering.  \n   - **Format**: Online and in-person (various U.S. locations).  \n   - **Known For**: Rigorous program with a focus on JavaScript and React.  \n\n5. **Le Wagon**  \n   - **Focus**: Full-stack development and data science.  \n   - **Format**: In-person (global locations) and online.  \n   - **Known For**: Strong emphasis on hands-on projects and entrepreneurship.  \n\n6. **Thinkful**  \n   - **Focus**: Software engineering, data science, UX/UI design, and more.  \n   - **Format**: Online.  \n   - **Known For**: One-on-one mentorship and flexible program options.  \n\n7. **Codesmith**  \n   - **Focus**: Software engineering (JavaScript, React, Node.js).  \n   - **Format**: Online and in-person (Los Angeles, New York City).  \n   - **Known For**: Focus on advanced engineering principles and open-source contributions.  \n\n8. **Springboard**  \n   - **Focus**: Software engineering, data science, UX/UI design, and more.  \n   - **Format**: Online.  \n   - **Known For**: Self-paced learning with mentorship and a job guarantee.  \n\n9. **Lambda School (Bloom Institute of Technology)**  \n   - **Focus**: Full-stack web development, data science, and more.  \n   - **Format**: Online.  \n   - **Known For**: Income share agreement (ISA) payment model.  \n\n10. **Tech Elevator**  \n    - **Focus**: Full-stack web development.  \n    - **Format**: In-person and online.  \n    - **Known For**: Strong focus on job preparation and career services.  \n\n---\n\n### Key Factors to Consider When Choosing a Bootcamp:  \n- **Curriculum**: Does it cover the skills and technologies you want to learn?  \n- **Outcomes**: What are the job placement rates and average salaries for graduates?  \n- **Format**: Do you prefer in-person, online, or a hybrid model?  \n- **Cost**: What\u2019s the tuition, and are there financing options or income share agreements?  \n- **Support**: Does the bootcamp offer career services, mentorship, and alumni networks?  \n- **Reputation**: Look for reviews on program experience and outcomes on platforms like **Course Report** or **SwitchUp**.  \n\n### Final Tip:  \nResearch thoroughly, talk to alumni, and consider taking free or low-cost introductory courses (like those on **freeCodeCamp**, **Codecademy**, or **Coursera**) to ensure coding bootcamp is the right path for you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
